  "title": "Warehouse Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p><p><ul><li>Provide support for daily store administrative operations, including the preparation of local purchase orders, receipt of transfer orders, goods receiving, and pick list generation.</li><li>Oversee inventory control activities and perform stock adjustments as required.</li><li>Ensure accurate and timely updates in the Warehouse Management System (WMS) using Microsoft 365.</li><li>Handle incoming calls from internal stakeholders and respond to their inquiries.</li><li>Prepare, update, and revise documents such as correspondence, reports, and emails.</li></ul></p></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Business Administration or any related field.</li><li>Minimum 1 year working experience as Warehouse position.</li><li>Excellent communication skills</li></ul><p>Interested applicants for the above advertised position(s), please kindly email an updated copy of your resume to: <strong>gs1@talenttradersg.com;</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>EA License No.: 13C6305</p><p>Registration No.: R23117856 CHOE KIN MUN</p><p><br /></p><p>For candidate who applied for the advertised position is deemed to have consented to us that we may collect, use or disclose your personal information for purpose in connection with the services provided by us.</p>",
